	<p class="cs7F45F1B"><span class="cs1489E706">Provided</span><span class="cs46AE26E6">, That the salary amounts used to determine any increases in compensation for elected county officials, as provided for in subsection (6) of this section, shall include any additional compensation received by those public officials pursuant to &sect;7-7-6b and &sect;11A-1-17 of this code.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs68EFC440">(8)</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> </span><span class="cs46AE26E6">(5)</span><span class="csEF05ACC"> Any county clerk, circuit clerk, county assessor, prosecuting attorney, or sheriff of a Class I through Class V county, inclusive, any assessor or any sheriff of a Class VI through Class IX county, inclusive, shall devote full time to his or her public duties to the exclusion of any other employment: </span><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Provided</span><span class="csEF05ACC">, That any public official whose term of office begins when his or her county&rsquo;s classification imposes no restriction on his or her outside activities may not be restricted on his or her outside activities during the remainder of the term for which he or she is elected.</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(6) On March 1, 2028, and every second year after that, the county commission of each county shall review the current salaries of all elected county officials who prevailed in the preceding general election and commenced a new full term of office and determine if the proposed annual county budget for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2028, has increased over the previous fiscal year in an amount sufficient for the payment of an increase in the salaries and the related employment taxes of all elected county officials who prevailed in the preceding general election and commenced a new full term of office by no less than two percent or a percentage not to exceed five percent per annum since the last increase in the compensation. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="cs46AE26E6">(7) If the proposed annual county budget for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2028, has increased over the previous fiscal year in an amount sufficient for the payment of an increase in the salaries and the related employment taxes of all elected county officials who prevailed in the preceding general election and commenced a new full term of office then the county commission shall fix the salary of all elected county officials who prevailed in the preceding general election and commenced a new full term of office at an annual rate of salary to which the elected county official is entitled pursuant to the effective salary upon commencement of a new term of office including an increase of no less than two percent but not to exceed five percent per annum since the last increase in the compensation. </span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs637BA255"><span class="cs7FA9C667">Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


